The testrail client will throw a TestRailError if you try to get a run by name, but there are multiple runs with the same name. This appears to happen because of this code:

```
    @run.register(str)
    @run.register(unicode)
    @singleresult
    def _run_by_name(self, name):
        return filter(lambda p: p.name.lower() == name.lower(), self.runs())
```

Specifically the `singleresult` decorator. While this decorator makes sense for the `run_by_id` method, which should only ever return a single entry, I don't feel it makes sense for `run_by_name`. It is entirely valid to have multiple runs in TestRail with the same name. `_run_by_name` should probably return all matching entries.

